07:48.719 --> 07:50.388
<i>How do you feel?</i>

07:53.516 --> 07:56.936
<i>The devil with yellow eyes.</i>

08:01.190 --> 08:03.192
<i>Is he here now?</i>

08:33.639 --> 08:36.100
Whoa, whoa, whoa,
I'm fine, I'm fine. I'm calm.

08:36.267 --> 08:39.854
I just had a bad dream.
And, guys, violence is not necessary.

08:40.021 --> 08:42.148
Needles are not necessary.

08:45.568 --> 08:47.320
<i>David?</i>

08:56.204 --> 08:58.456
How does that make you feel?

09:00.082 --> 09:02.084
I mean, it's just....

09:02.335 --> 09:03.920
It's fine.

09:04.086 --> 09:05.713
Like, whatever.

09:05.880 --> 09:08.341
Because, I mean, look at me.
I know what I am.

09:08.507 --> 09:11.135
- And what's that?
- Well, you know.

09:14.180 --> 09:16.724
What happened. What I did...

09:18.017 --> 09:19.560
...to Dr. Poole.

09:20.186 --> 09:23.231
- You went off your medications.
- But that's not....

09:29.904 --> 09:31.197
That's....

09:32.031 --> 09:33.699
You know, I....

09:34.033 --> 09:35.076
I saw things.

09:35.243 --> 09:37.370
Delusions, you mean.
We talked about that.

09:37.536 --> 09:39.413
Your brain chemistry...

09:39.580 --> 09:42.375
- Hey, yeah.
- ...your illness simulates voices.

09:42.541 --> 09:45.962
All the hallucinations you described...

09:46.128 --> 09:48.714
- ...the devil with yellow eyes.
- Hmm.

09:50.258 --> 09:52.426
You have something to add?

09:53.135 --> 09:54.804
No.

09:56.180 --> 09:57.807
Please keep talking.

09:57.974 --> 10:01.811
So we can all pretend that our problems
are just in our heads.

10:03.479 --> 10:05.398
What does that mean?

10:09.652 --> 10:13.698
It means that you're in here
because somebody said you're not normal.

10:14.031 --> 10:17.368
Like normal is this suit
we're all supposed to....

10:18.327 --> 10:20.621
But you know who else wasn't normal?
Picasso.

10:20.788 --> 10:23.749
- Einstein.
- Ooh, I like her.

10:23.916 --> 10:25.793
I like you.

10:25.960 --> 10:28.754
You got what the kids these days
call moxie.

10:29.130 --> 10:33.092
You know, just so I'm clear, are you
Einstein or Picasso in this scenario?

10:33.259 --> 10:35.136
Whatever.

10:35.303 --> 10:37.638
All I'm saying is...

10:38.597 --> 10:41.225
...what if your problems
aren't in your head?

10:42.601 --> 10:45.104
What if they aren't even problems?

10:46.731 --> 10:49.608
- Talk about that.
- No, I'm good.

10:50.651 --> 10:54.155
I read in your file
that you don't like to be touched.

10:58.326 --> 11:02.705
All animals need physical contact
to feel love.

11:06.667 --> 11:09.920
You know those cartoons
in, like, magazines?

11:10.087 --> 11:12.590
There's a man on an island with,
like, maybe a single palm tree.

11:12.757 --> 11:13.758
Hmm.

11:13.924 --> 11:17.595
People say go to your happy place,
and that's what I think about.

11:18.846 --> 11:20.931
- Well, that's sad.
- That's sad?

11:23.392 --> 11:25.853
You're in a mental hospital.

11:27.438 --> 11:29.148
All I'm saying is...

11:30.816 --> 11:34.111
...that thing they tell us is crazy.

11:34.945 --> 11:39.492
How I don't wanna be handled.

11:40.576 --> 11:44.997
Or you see stuff
and hear whatever voices.

11:46.832 --> 11:49.126
That's what makes you you.

11:59.678 --> 12:02.098
Do you wanna be my girlfriend?

12:08.938 --> 12:10.523
Okay.

12:11.774 --> 12:14.485
But don't touch me.

12:15.569 --> 12:16.946
Okay.

12:22.326 --> 12:23.953
Yeah?

12:24.495 --> 12:26.163
Yeah.

12:27.498 --> 12:29.166
Okay.

12:32.545 --> 12:34.547
Find me at dinner.

12:43.514 --> 12:45.683
Why are the hot ones always so crazy?

12:53.482 --> 12:56.819
<i>She comes in colors everywhere</i>

12:56.986 --> 13:02.825
<i>She combs her hair
She's like a rainbow</i>

13:02.992 --> 13:05.911
<i>Coming, colors in the air</i>

13:06.078 --> 13:10.583
<i>Oh, everywhere
She comes in colors</i>

13:19.258 --> 13:22.511
- No cherries.
- I live on cherry pie. It's incredible.

13:22.678 --> 13:26.807
I don't like orange-flavored things,
and I don't like cherry-flavored things.

13:26.974 --> 13:31.562
This has pretty much everything you need.
It has, like, crust and cherries.

13:35.024 --> 13:38.402
<i>She comes in colors everywhere</i>

13:38.569 --> 13:40.362
<i>She combs her hair</i>

13:40.529 --> 13:44.158
<i>She's like a rainbow</i>

13:44.325 --> 13:46.619
<i>Coming, colors in the air</i>

13:47.119 --> 13:53.042
<i>Oh, everywhere
She comes in colors</i>

14:38.712 --> 14:40.923
I see you.

14:43.092 --> 14:45.261
This is your spot, huh?

14:49.765 --> 14:52.560
After the sun goes down...

14:54.186 --> 14:56.564
...when the light is right...

14:57.356 --> 14:59.191
...if you...

15:01.318 --> 15:04.530
...kind of un-focus your eyes...

15:06.532 --> 15:07.950
...like this. See?

15:10.286 --> 15:12.580
- That's charming.
- Shut up.

15:14.540 --> 15:16.292
Now you.

15:20.421 --> 15:22.715
And then look back out.

15:31.640 --> 15:34.560
You see how the hospital disappears?

15:36.312 --> 15:38.814
You can see yourself down there.

15:41.650 --> 15:43.319
Like...

15:43.694 --> 15:45.779
...you're in here...

15:47.197 --> 15:49.950
...watching yourself outside.

15:52.453 --> 15:53.579
What are you doing?

15:53.746 --> 15:56.498
Keep calm. I'm not gonna touch you.

15:56.957 --> 16:01.003
Just hold still and look out the window.

16:22.066 --> 16:24.068
<i>David.</i>

16:24.485 --> 16:28.197
How long were you together?
You and the girl who disappeared?

16:28.364 --> 16:29.740
She didn't disappear.

16:30.324 --> 16:32.785
I told you, they took her.

16:32.951 --> 16:34.453
Sydney Barrett, the girl?

16:35.204 --> 16:38.874
Yes. Look, uh, talk to the hospital.
They've got records.

16:39.041 --> 16:41.877
The hospital where you were a patient
the past six years...

16:42.044 --> 16:45.673
...after being diagnosed
with paranoid schizophrenia?

16:45.839 --> 16:49.176
Yes, but my condition
has nothing to do with that.

16:49.343 --> 16:52.846
I didn't make her up. She's a real girl.
A woman.

16:55.265 --> 16:58.686
- Call the hospital. They've got records.
- We've spoken to the hospital.

16:58.852 --> 17:02.481
They have no record of Sydney Barrett
ever being a patient there.

17:06.694 --> 17:12.116
Look, is it possible, Mr. Haller--?
And I'm not a psychiatrist, so....

17:12.282 --> 17:16.662
But is it possible that this whole thing,
the girl, the incident...

17:16.829 --> 17:18.789
...that it's just part of your illness?

17:18.956 --> 17:20.999
- A delusion?
- Uh, yes.

17:21.166 --> 17:22.501
Sure, uh, fine.

17:22.668 --> 17:24.169
Um....

17:24.336 --> 17:28.340
Well, how do you explain
what happened to Lenny?

17:28.841 --> 17:30.175
Well, all of them.

17:30.342 --> 17:33.053
Well, I can't.
That's why we're having this.

17:33.220 --> 17:35.514
Talk to Dr. Kissinger. He knows.

17:36.640 --> 17:39.268
And Dr. Kissinger was your psychiatrist?

17:39.435 --> 17:40.853
Yes.

17:41.019 --> 17:44.398
Ahem, somehow, I have a hard time
believing your psychiatrist...

17:44.565 --> 17:47.234
...is gonna confirm the story
that you're telling me now.

17:48.068 --> 17:51.488
Well, David, I think, don't you,
that we should talk about it?

17:51.655 --> 17:53.574
Hmm? No.

17:53.741 --> 17:57.453
It's important you-- If you wanna go home--
You see, my job--

17:57.619 --> 17:58.746
Part of my job...

17:59.747 --> 18:01.540
...is to assess.

18:01.707 --> 18:04.293
Are you still a danger to yourself?
To others?

18:04.460 --> 18:07.087
And the fact that you tried
to hang yourself.

18:07.254 --> 18:09.840
- We can skip that part.
- Hmm?

18:10.883 --> 18:13.010
Unless you think it's relevant too.

18:13.177 --> 18:15.596
No. We don't have to.

18:22.686 --> 18:24.980
Interesting. Okay.

18:25.147 --> 18:26.523
Let's talk about it.

18:29.318 --> 18:32.654
Uh, well, I, uh, had a hard time after college...

18:32.821 --> 18:36.450
...after I got expelled.

18:36.700 --> 18:38.368
I wasn't thinking straight.

18:40.078 --> 18:43.999
<i>The voices and, uh, not sleeping.</i>

18:45.417 --> 18:47.669
<i>And I was angry all the....</i>

18:48.670 --> 18:51.507
<i>- And then Philly left.</i>
- David, you okay?

18:54.718 --> 18:57.805
And I decided, you know...

18:57.971 --> 18:59.890
...what was the point?

19:00.766 --> 19:03.936
When a blade breaks, you don't fix it.
You just get another blade.

19:04.102 --> 19:06.980
So I tied a knot.

19:07.147 --> 19:09.399
<i>- David, stop. Stop.
- Don't touch it.</i>

19:09.566 --> 19:11.318
<i>- Don't.
- Stupid, stupid.</i>

19:11.735 --> 19:13.570
Did the voices tell you to do that?

19:13.737 --> 19:16.031
No. No.

19:16.198 --> 19:18.534
No, they tried to stop me.

19:18.700 --> 19:20.452
They didn't like it.

19:20.786 --> 19:23.956
<i>And yet the police say
they found no noose in the apartment.</i>

19:25.040 --> 19:26.667
<i>Just rope burns on your neck.</i>

19:33.674 --> 19:35.342
How do you feel now?

19:37.094 --> 19:38.637
Uh....

19:38.804 --> 19:40.764
Better.

19:41.098 --> 19:42.683
Well, let me ask you this.

19:42.850 --> 19:46.854
Do you still feel that, quote:

19:47.354 --> 19:51.233
"You have power over things
and can control things with your mind"?

19:53.694 --> 19:54.736
<i>Hold on.</i>

19:55.404 --> 19:58.073
You think you can control things
with your mind?

19:58.240 --> 20:00.075
I did at one point.

20:00.242 --> 20:01.994
But they help with that, the drugs.

20:02.160 --> 20:04.913
- Is that why I'm here? Is that what this is?
- David.

20:05.080 --> 20:08.083
You think I did this?
That I killed her with my mind?

20:08.250 --> 20:11.545
No. Don't be ridiculous, but....

20:12.254 --> 20:14.464
The girl is dead, David. She is.

20:14.631 --> 20:17.342
And it wasn't a heart attack, right?

20:17.509 --> 20:20.012
So we're just...

20:20.262 --> 20:23.181
...uh, looking for the truth...

20:24.224 --> 20:25.726
...which you promised to tell.

20:27.603 --> 20:29.187
Look.

20:29.354 --> 20:30.939
I don't know, okay?

20:31.106 --> 20:35.152
It's-- It's fuzzy. It's....

20:35.736 --> 20:37.654
That's okay.

20:38.071 --> 20:40.657
Just tell me what happened next.

21:23.325 --> 21:24.493
Boo.

21:26.787 --> 21:28.580
Jeez.

21:28.914 --> 21:30.290
- What are you doing?
- Shh.

21:31.917 --> 21:34.044
- Can you be in here?
- Don't be a pussy.

21:34.544 --> 21:36.421
Lie back.

21:43.220 --> 21:44.429
No, I'll be on top.

21:44.888 --> 21:46.473
All right.

21:46.640 --> 21:48.100
Yeah.

22:08.286 --> 22:10.831
I'm getting out tomorrow.

22:15.085 --> 22:16.628
What?

22:18.630 --> 22:21.133
Kissinger says I'm clean.

22:22.342 --> 22:24.636
So I get to go home.

22:36.231 --> 22:38.358
Good. That's good.

22:53.040 --> 22:55.333
You've got to get better.

22:55.792 --> 22:57.377
Okay?

23:00.088 --> 23:02.257
So you can come home too.

23:25.030 --> 23:27.365
<i>And why couldn't you touch her?</i>

23:27.783 --> 23:28.950
Well, she was--

23:29.117 --> 23:31.995
You know, it's a mental hospital.
People have issues.

23:32.162 --> 23:34.664
I mean, that's what I thought then.

23:34.831 --> 23:36.625
- Now--
- Uh, how long were you together...

23:36.792 --> 23:39.586
- ...before the incident?
- Can we take a break?

23:40.378 --> 23:41.671
Please, I-- Just--

23:41.838 --> 23:44.549
Without the meds,
it's really hard to keep things....

23:44.716 --> 23:48.386
Of course. And there's, uh, food coming.

23:48.553 --> 23:50.889
I promise. But let's take a break.

23:52.015 --> 23:53.892
We'll pick this up again in 30 minutes.

24:06.738 --> 24:07.989
Cue the phone.

24:27.968 --> 24:32.264
<i>Floor to Bravo Tango,
inside the building. Building is secure.</i>

24:47.863 --> 24:51.700
Very, very good. It's a real surprise.

24:51.867 --> 24:52.951
How does it look?

24:53.118 --> 24:55.829
He's twitchy.

24:55.996 --> 24:58.248
- You said he was off his meds?
- For a week now.

24:58.415 --> 25:01.293
They think that may be why
the spike in telepathic activity.

25:01.459 --> 25:03.420
So is he crazy, or...?

25:03.587 --> 25:06.715
Well, I think he's telling the truth
as he knows it.

25:06.882 --> 25:09.759
- Meaning?
- Well, he believes he's mentally ill.

25:09.926 --> 25:14.389
But at the same time, part of him knows
that the power is real.

25:14.556 --> 25:18.476
And are we clear
on the scope and nature of this power?

25:18.643 --> 25:22.522
No, but if the readings are right,
he may be the most powerful mutant...

25:22.689 --> 25:25.233
- ...that we have ever encountered.
- Hmm.

25:25.609 --> 25:29.905
After what happened in Red Hook,
I'd say that's an understatement.

25:31.740 --> 25:34.201
So he has the power...

25:34.367 --> 25:40.373
...but he doesn't understand it
or know how to control it?

25:40.540 --> 25:43.168
I'd like to dig deeper,
see if we can figure out what triggers him.

25:43.335 --> 25:45.587
Division One thinks we should kill him.

25:45.754 --> 25:49.549
Now, before he realizes what he is.

25:49.716 --> 25:52.844
- We may never get the chance again.
- That would be a mistake.

25:53.011 --> 25:56.181
We've never had a subject
like this before. I mean....

25:57.057 --> 25:58.558
Look.

25:58.767 --> 26:01.102
Just give me until the end of the day...

26:01.269 --> 26:03.813
...and you have the gas if you need it.

26:05.607 --> 26:07.150
<i>Okay.</i>

26:07.317 --> 26:12.197
<i>But if he so much as farts too loud,
we're moving to level two.</i>

26:36.888 --> 26:38.807
Could I be alone?

27:07.961 --> 27:10.046
